<quantity box="[1336,1452,1150,1174]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2999999999999998" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" unit="mm" value="1.2999999999999998" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.2">1.2-1.4 mm</quantity>
, black, ovate to narrow-ovate (
<figureCitation box="[1096,1151,1176,1201]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[132,143,797,814]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,93,755]" captionTargetId="figure-607@6.[132,1455,215,755]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 3. — Allium izmirense Pirhan, sp. nov.: A, B, pollen grains; C, details of pollen surface in SEM photos; D, seed; E, F, details of seed testa in SEM photos. Scale bars: A, 30 µm; B, 10 µm; C, 3 µm; D, 1 mm; E, 500 µm; F, 200 µm." pageId="3" pageNumber="134">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Testa surface has irregular and elongated polygonal testa cells. Periclinal walls bearing several verrucae and mostly one larger central verruca combined with depressed and striate anticlinal walls were also present. Anticlinal walls flat, with irregularly-shaped granules and flat verrucae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[806,1458,465,2027]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">
POLLEN MORPHOLOGY. — Pollen grains yellowish, as monads; prolate; exine ornamentation microrugulate and microperforate; equatorial axis (E) roughly 25 to 30 µm long; polar axis (P) roughly 14 to 18 µm wide (
<figureCitation box="[1002,1058,1410,1434]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[132,143,797,814]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,93,755]" captionTargetId="figure-607@6.[132,1455,215,755]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 3. — Allium izmirense Pirhan, sp. nov.: A, B, pollen grains; C, details of pollen surface in SEM photos; D, seed; E, F, details of seed testa in SEM photos. Scale bars: A, 30 µm; B, 10 µm; C, 3 µm; D, 1 mm; E, 500 µm; F, 200 µm." pageId="3" pageNumber="134">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="134" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[806,1458,465,2027]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">
ETYMOLOGY. — The species epithet is derived from 
<collectingRegion box="[1307,1452,1458,1485]" country="Turkey" name="Izmir" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">İzmir Province</collectingRegion>
, where the new species was first discovered. The Turkish name of this species is given as “tiresoğanI”, according to the guidelines of 
<bibRefCitation author="MENEMEN Y. &amp; AYTAC Z. &amp; KANDEMIR A." box="[814,1039,1537,1561]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" pagination="28 - 31" refId="ref5774" refString="MENEMEN Y., AYTAC Z. &amp; KANDEMIR A. 2013. - Turkce bilimsel bitki adlarI yonergesi. Bagbahce Dergisi 47: 28 - 31." type="journal article" year="2013">
Menemen 
<emphasis box="[918,965,1537,1561]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="134" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[806,1458,465,2027]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">
<materialsCitation country="Turkey" county="Tire" elevation="1083" location="Mountain" municipality="Kaplan Village" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Aydin">
DISTRIBUTION, 
<subScript attach="right" box="[963,1183,1591,1608]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">HABITAT AND ECOLOGY</subScript>
. — 
<taxonomicName authority="Pirhan, 2022" authorityName="Pirhan" authorityYear="2022" box="[1222,1378,1585,1609]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="izmirense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1222,1378,1585,1609]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">Allium izmirense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1384,1456,1585,1608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a local endemic to the 
<collectingRegion box="[1066,1126,1611,1635]" country="Turkey" name="Aydin" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">AydIn</collectingRegion>
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03815B5CFF94FFEBE082FE8DFE18F8B3:8EF7BC91FF94FFEEE756F9B1FB1AF9FC" box="[1134,1234,1611,1635]" country="Turkey" county="Tire" municipality="Kaplan Village" name="Mountain" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" stateProvince="Aydin">Mountain</location>
range, which extends across both 
<collectingRegion box="[933,986,1639,1665]" country="Turkey" name="Izmir" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">İzmir</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1038,1097,1638,1662]" country="Turkey" name="Aydin" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">AydIn</collectingRegion>
in western 
<collectingCountry box="[1214,1299,1638,1662]" name="Turkey" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
, and belongs to the element of the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03815B5CFF94FFEBE082FE8DFE18F8B3:8EF7BC91FF94FFEEE0DCF97AFBBCF907" box="[996,1140,1664,1688]" country="Turkey" county="Tire" municipality="Kaplan Village" name="Mediterranean" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" stateProvince="Aydin">Mediterranean</location>
floristic region. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03815B5CFF94FFEBE082FE8DFE18F8B3:8EF7BC91FF94FFEEE62AF97BFAEAF907" box="[1298,1314,1665,1688]" country="Turkey" county="Tire" municipality="Kaplan Village" name="It" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" stateProvince="Aydin">It</location>
colonizes only calcareous rocks above 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1029,1169,1691,1715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">Kaplan Village</collectingMunicipality>
in the district of 
<collectingCounty box="[1327,1370,1691,1715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">Tire</collectingCounty>
, in 
<collectingRegion box="[1402,1454,1692,1718]" country="Turkey" name="Izmir" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">İzmir</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[821,877,1717,1741]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="7.[132,143,876,893]" captionText="FIG. 4. — Distribution map of Allium izmirense Pirhan, sp. nov. (), A. stamineum Boiss. (), A. armenum Boiss. (), A. tchihatschewii subsp. dumanii (Koyuncu &amp; Koçyigit) Yild. (), A. hoshabicum Fırat (), and A. huber-morathii Kollman ()." pageId="3" pageNumber="134">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), preferably with an eastern to northeastern orientation, at elevations of 
<quantity box="[941,1080,1744,1768]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0825" metricValueMax="1.115" metricValueMin="1.05" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" unit="m" value="1082.5" valueMax="1115.0" valueMin="1050.0">
<elevation box="[941,1080,1744,1768]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0825" metricValueMax="1.115" metricValueMin="1.05" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" unit="m" value="1082.5" valueMax="1115.0" valueMin="1050.0">1050-1115 m</elevation>
</quantity>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[806,1458,465,2027]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">
SPECIES CONSERVATION ASSESSMENT. — The new species has a very restricted distribution. The area of occupancy for 
<taxonomicName authority="Pirhan, 2022" authorityName="Pirhan" authorityYear="2022" box="[1296,1455,1818,1842]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="izmirense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1296,1455,1818,1842]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">Allium izmirense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[813,888,1845,1868]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was calculated as 
<quantity box="[1064,1159,1844,1869]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" unit="km" value="0.025">0.025 km</quantity>
2, in which about 300-350 individuals were estimated to occur. Overgrazing by sheep and goat herds was observed. There was also a high anthropogenic effect on 
<taxonomicName authority="Pirhan, 2022" authorityName="Pirhan" authorityYear="2022" box="[813,931,1924,1948]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="izmirense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[813,931,1924,1948]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">A. izmirense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[939,1017,1924,1947]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
due to the existence of a wind power plant installed within the population. According to the IUCN criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[821,948,1977,2001]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" refId="ref5317" refString="IUCN 2016. - Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 11. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee, Cambridge U. K. Available online: http: // jr. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 22 December 2020)" type="url" year="2016">IUCN 2016</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Pirhan, 2022" authorityName="Pirhan" authorityYear="2022" box="[971,1093,1977,2001]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="izmirense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[971,1093,1977,2001]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">A. izmirense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1101,1180,1977,2000]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was evaluated as Critically Endangered (CR) B2ab (ii,iii,v).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
